  "prompt": "What are some of the best Soft Rock songs of all time?",
  "response": "Soft rock has produced many timeless and beloved songs over the years. Here are some of the best soft rock songs of all time:\n\n1. **Eagles - \"Hotel California\" (1976)**\n   - A hauntingly beautiful track that tells a story of excess and disillusionment, \"Hotel California\" is a staple in soft rock and classic rock genres.\n\n2. **Simon & Garfunkel - \"Bridge Over Troubled Water\" (1970)**\n   - Known for its soothing melody and powerful vocals, this song has become an iconic representation of comfort and support.\n\n3. **Fleetwood Mac - \"Dreams\" (1977)**\n   - A melodic and emotionally charged song that showcases the unique chemistry of the band, \"Dreams\" is a classic from the Rumours album.\n\n4. **Elton John - \"Your Song\" (1970)**\n   - A romantic ballad that captures the simplicity and beauty of expressing love through song, \"Your Song\" is one of Elton John's most celebrated works.\n\n5. **James Taylor - \"Fire and Rain\" (1970)**\n   - An introspective and emotionally resonant track, \"Fire and Rain\" showcases James Taylor's signature soft rock style and heartfelt lyrics.\n\n6. **Carly Simon - \"You're So Vain\" (1972)**\n   - A catchy and witty song that combines soft rock with a touch of pop, \"You're So Vain\" is one of Carly Simon's most famous hits.\n\n7. **Cat Stevens - \"Wild World\" (1970)**\n   - A gentle and melancholic track, \"Wild World\" captures the essence of soft rock with its soothing melody and introspective lyrics.\n\n8. **America - \"A Horse with No Name\" (1971)**\n   - Known for its hypnotic rhythm and evocative lyrics, this song is a quintessential soft rock hit that transports listeners to a desert landscape.\n\n9. **The Doobie Brothers - \"What a Fool Believes\" (1978)**\n   - A smooth and soulful track, \"What a Fool Believes\" combines soft rock elements with a touch of R&B, earning it a Grammy for Song of the Year.\n\n10. **Toto - \"Africa\" (1982)**\n    - With its iconic chorus and memorable synthesizer riff, \"Africa\" is a soft rock classic that remains popular across generations.\n\nThese songs represent the best of the soft rock genre, showcasing the soothing melodies, heartfelt lyrics, and emotional depth that define the style.",
